Good pizza great value overall.  The lunch specials are great!  You can’t beat 2 slices, 2 drinks and 4 motz sticks for $7.99!  The food is fast, it’s not much to look at.  I like the sausage aka cheese the best.  The people working there are amazing too!
Really like this spot! I usually get the classic Chicago square cut and a salad. It's a really reasonable price and the staff is really friendly. Ordering online is super fast and easy too.

I love thin crust pizza and have heard good things about Home Team so have been wanting to try this place for a while, and finally did so last week.  It was AWESOME.  The promo for the 16" pizza for pickup is a great deal, and left room for me to order some other things, all which were super tasty.  The pickup process is super easy and safe-  you pay through a small walk-up window and they give you your food through another sliding glass window.   I also appreciate that they call you when your order is ready.  The food was hot, fresh, tasty, and everything I wanted it to be.  Lastly, the woman working was so sweet... friendly, quick, and offered a very genuine 'thank you' - when, in my opinion, the thanks should go to them.   SUPPORT LOCAL, SUPPORT HOME TEAM!

With all the love in my heart I really hate this place. And in this day in age with the frivolous lawsuits that actually win.. I truly believe I have a case against them for making me more fat. The pizza is delicious the prices cant be beat, the walk up window is perfect, the staff is great. seriously 100 percent their fault that I find myself going there at least 2-3 times a week,  I've gained more then then quarantine 15, more like the quarantine 25.... Thanks for being AWESOME Home Team Pizza, but now I must sue you...

Home Team has all the elements of a fantastic Chicago pizza place.  -Their pizza is downright tasty. I'm a pepperoni fan myself and their thin crust doesn't disappoint.  -It's cut into squares, like a proper Chicago pizza should be.  -It's CHEAP. Seriously, pizza this good and this cheap is extremely hard to find.  -It's fast. Orders are usually done in about 20 minutes.  -They also have great ice cream and shakes.  -Their owners are fantastic people and very supportive of the community.

Yum, yum and uh YUM! I can't contain my joy. I stopped eating pork about 15 years ago and have been on the search for a replacement to the good ol' sausage and mushroom pizza. Well, look no further than Hometeam Pizza. They don't have pork in their facility and make all sausage and pepperoni in house without casings.. I will not go anywhere else, again. pizza and goodies all fresh and promptly delivered.  No worries I'm spreading the word on this local Gem. Added review: Ok, in addition to pizza I had the fried pickles for the 1st time last week. I think those were homemade pickles I just had. SAY WHAT!? The mushrooms were plump and not slimy on my pizza. This place is refreshing since when I order pizza it's never greasy.  All compliments of some flavored soda.  Not an RC or cola kind of place. Granted, I'm certain they make it available. Just ask. Also,  they need to start jarring their homemade giardiniera relish. FRESH, perfect oil to veggie ratio.  Yum. Can't contain my enjoyment of this establishment.

A top pizza place for thin crust in Chicago  highly recommend.
